 <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  The sign for "sit" uses a single motion.  This is part of a noun/verb pair.  If you use a double
motion it means "chair."
 </p>
 <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  <br/>
  SIT:
  <br/>
  <img border="0" src="../../gifs/s/sit.gif" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto" width="480"/>
  <font face="Arial">
   <img border="0" height="320" src="../../signjpegs/c/chair-03.jpg" width="320"/>
   <img border="0" height="320" src="../../signjpegs/c/chair-04.jpg" width="320"/>
  </font>
 </p>
 <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  <iframe allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZvzKTn4qWfA?rel=0" width="560">
  </iframe>
 </p>
 <font face="Arial">
  <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
   SIT (anxious version 1):
  </p>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
